\i \cf0 To execute outside the VC++ environment, using the CLSW emulator for input packets:
\i0 \
\
1) In the 'Solution Explorer' right-click 'CreateStandaloneGripMMI' and select \'91Clean\'92.\
2) In the 'Solution Explorer' right-click 'CreateStandaloneGripMMI' and select 'Build'.\
3) Exit Microsoft Visual C++.\
3) Navigate to the \'93GripMMI (version)\\GripExecutables\'94 directory.\
4) Execute the GripMMI in simulation mode by double clicking RunGripMMI.bat.\
   This will run the CLWS emulator to send out recorded packet to the Grip MMI.\
   It will use the directory \'93GripMMI (version)\\GripCache\'94 to store packet files.\
   \
Note that you can edit RunGripMMI.bat to change the source file for the pre-recorded packet files or to change to \'91constructed\'92 mode. The module GripGroundMonitorClient stores all packets received from the CLWS server or the emulator in the cache directory with a filename of the form GripPacketsYYYY.MM.DD.any.gpk. Any of these files can be substituted for the default source file for the pre-recorded packets. Thus, one can use the packets recorded from any session using the real GRIP hardware to provide packets for further testing using the emulator.\
\
