\b\fs28 \cf0 To install the Grip Ground MMI on a machine for execution only
\b0 :\

\fs24 \
0) Install the Microsoft runtime libraries  that can be found in "GripMMI (version)\\GripInstallItems:\
	vcredist_x86 (VS2010 Redistributable Official English).exe \
	dotNetFx40_Client_x86_x64.exe\
Step 0 is necessary only if Microsoft Visual C++ 2010 Express is not already installed on the machine in question.\
\
1) On the development machine, Build the GripMMI solution in \'91Release\'92 mode.\
2) Select a location for the executable files. Copy \'93GripMMI (version)\\GripExecutables\'94 from the development installation to that location.\
3) Select a location for the Grip Script files. Copy \'93GripMMI (version)\\GripScripts\'94 from the development installation to that location.\
\
NB The script files are read-only for the MMI program and so they could be installed in the same location as the executable files. However, one might conceivably wish to change the scripts without changing the executables, for example, to run a sim with scripts other than the flight scripts. You might therefore wish to install the script files in a location that has read/write access.\
\
4) Select a location for the real-time data packet cache files. \
\
5) Edit GripExecutables\\RunGripMMI.bat to: \
\
	1) to enable or inhibit the execution of the CLWS emulator.\
	2) to set the IP address or host name of the CLWS server (or emulator).\
	2) set the full path to the cache file directory (CacheDir), \
	3) set the location of the GRIP Scirpts (ScriptDir) and \
	4) to select the alternate EPM Software Unit ID  if running two clients off of the same CLWS server.\
\
6) Execute RunGripMMI.bat. \
\
This will launch 2 processes: GripGroundMonitorClient.exe, which listens for packets from the CLWS server and stores them in the cache files and GripMMI.exe which displays the cached data on the screen. If configured to use the CLWS emulator for testing purposed, it will also launch CLWSemulator.exe.\
